TY  - JOUR
T1  - Steady Endogenous Growth with Population and R & D Inputs Growing
AU  - Howitt, Peter
Y1  - 1999/08/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/250076
DO  - 10.1086/250076
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 715
EP  - 730
VL  - 107
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper presents a Schumpeterian endogenous growth model in which a steady state exists with a constant growth rate even though population and the inputs to R. & D. are growing. The scale effect of rising population is nullified by product proliferation that fragments the growing demand for intermediate prodcuts, thus preventing the reward to any specific innovation from rising with population. All the ususal comparitive statics results of Schumpeterian growth theory are valid, including the positive effect of R. & D. subsidies on growth.
AB  - This paper presents a Schumpeterian endogenous growth model in which a steady state exists with a constant growth rate even though population and the inputs to R. & D. are growing. The scale effect of rising population is nullified by product proliferation that fragments the growing demand for intermediate prodcuts, thus preventing the reward to any specific innovation from rising with population. All the ususal comparitive statics results of Schumpeterian growth theory are valid, including the positive effect of R. & D. subsidies on growth.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/250076
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/250076
Y2  - 2024/03/22
